34
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:34,651
You're not sulking?

35
00:04:34,717 --> 00:04:36,563
Well, then what's the problem?

36
00:04:51,812 --> 00:04:52,672
Um...

37
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:57,031
You can use your words to talk
to me if you really need to.

38
00:05:31,888 --> 00:05:32,735
Here I come!

39
00:05:58,022 --> 00:05:58,363
Yes!

40
00:05:58,388 --> 00:05:59,823
I don't think so!

41
00:05:59,848 --> 00:06:01,612
But I jumped on the mat without touching the bar, so...

42
00:06:01,637 --> 00:06:03,029
Yeah, you made it past the bar.

43
00:06:03,054 --> 00:06:04,228
By going under it!

44
00:06:04,432 --> 00:06:06,144
How many times do I have to repeat myself?

45
00:06:06,169 --> 00:06:07,654
You have to get over the bar!

46
00:06:07,679 --> 00:06:08,362
Sorry.

47
00:06:08,554 --> 00:06:10,399
I'll do it right this time, I swear.

48
00:06:11,128 --> 00:06:13,100
Here, I'll lower it to make things easier.

49
00:06:13,618 --> 00:06:14,868
Take it nice and slow.

50
00:06:14,893 --> 00:06:17,204
And remember the jumping form I taught you before.

51
00:06:17,464 --> 00:06:18,017
Okay!

52
00:06:18,598 --> 00:06:19,477
This is it.

53
00:06:19,534 --> 00:06:23,097
I've gotta at least be able to make it
over the bar when it's that freakin' low.

54
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:28,604
If I can't even pull this off, everyone'll laugh at me!

55
00:06:35,374 --> 00:06:36,591
Did I do it?

56
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:39,644
You ding-dong!

57
00:06:39,768 --> 00:06:41,571
Why can't you do the "thing" like I taught you?

58
00:06:41,596 --> 00:06:42,970
Do you just not get it?

59
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:47,066
Well, I can see me doing a proper Fosbury flop in my head.

60
00:06:48,368 --> 00:06:49,885
Oh, you're flopping all right.

61
00:06:50,141 --> 00:06:53,564
What you're doing is more like a Fosbury... torpedo!

62
00:06:55,846 --> 00:06:57,737
A human... torpedo.

63
00:06:57,762 --> 00:06:59,058
I wouldn't put it like that!

64
00:06:59,417 --> 00:07:01,020
No, wait.

65
00:07:01,482 --> 00:07:04,581
Actually... I think I just did.

66
00:07:05,339 --> 00:07:07,247
I'm not that bad, come on!

67
00:07:07,346 --> 00:07:08,346
Quit joking!

68
00:07:08,371 --> 00:07:09,753
But you are that bad!

69
00:07:11,689 --> 00:07:12,606
Sorry.

70
00:07:12,915 --> 00:07:16,336
Hey, don't apologize. I'll be right
here to help you out until you get it.

71
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:20,785
You're the one who's always
helping me out with my homework.

72
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:22,625
And now it's my turn to help you!

73
00:07:23,344 --> 00:07:25,467
I'm gonna stay by your side, no matter what!

74
00:07:27,194 --> 00:07:28,945
Try not to psych yourself out!

75
00:07:29,452 --> 00:07:31,859
Just relax a bit and take your time with it, okay?

76
00:07:32,259 --> 00:07:33,843
You totally got this thing!

77
00:07:33,868 --> 00:07:35,652
I believe in you, Mio!

78
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:40,950
I've always been bad at sports,

79
00:07:41,012 --> 00:07:42,810
for as long as I can remember.

80
00:07:45,105 --> 00:07:46,496
I hate to break it to you, Mio,

81
00:07:46,578 --> 00:07:48,569
but you're playing the wrong kind of football right now!

82
00:07:48,721 --> 00:07:51,207
I can be just as athletic as anyone else.

83
00:07:51,376 --> 00:07:53,876
But, whenever I have to follow any rules,

84
00:07:53,945 --> 00:07:55,601
everything falls apart!

85
00:07:56,134 --> 00:07:56,998
Get ready!

86
00:07:57,666 --> 00:07:59,212
And... fall!

87
00:07:59,829 --> 00:08:01,870
You're supposed to fall backwards on your back!

88
00:08:02,134 --> 00:08:05,107
But... that doesn't mean I can't change.

89
00:08:05,419 --> 00:08:06,540
I can be better!

90
00:08:06,925 --> 00:08:08,743
I just have to try!

91
00:08:09,492 --> 00:08:10,923
One, two...

92
00:08:12,188 --> 00:08:14,033
There! Huh?

93
00:08:14,058 --> 00:08:16,642
Mio, you are literally spinning out of control!

94
00:08:16,770 --> 00:08:18,601
I don't care how long it takes.

95
00:08:18,842 --> 00:08:20,940
I don't care if I keep failing!

96
00:08:32,202 --> 00:08:35,372
At least there's one thing I know I can do.

97
00:08:35,402 --> 00:08:36,892
I'll never give up!

98
00:08:36,964 --> 00:08:39,464
One, two, three!

99
00:08:41,471 --> 00:08:42,907
Well, almost.

100
00:08:42,932 --> 00:08:44,407
Let's try it one more time.

101
00:08:44,432 --> 00:08:46,087
Yuuko believes in me.

102
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:48,330
I think I'm gonna take a quick breather, 'kay?

103
00:08:48,355 --> 00:08:49,579
Sure, go ahead.

104
00:08:55,571 --> 00:08:57,434
So, I can believe in me!

105
00:08:58,753 --> 00:09:00,420
I'll give it everything I've got!

106
00:09:00,549 --> 00:09:01,896
I won't quit!

107
00:09:06,215 --> 00:09:09,325
I can be better if I keep on trying!

108
00:09:11,006 --> 00:09:13,376
Great effort can take you to even greater heights.

109
00:10:00,576 --> 00:10:04,953
And thus, the "Torpedo Flop" was born.

110
00:10:16,965 --> 00:10:19,090
The Life of White Tigers!

111
00:10:19,207 --> 00:10:20,102
Check 'em out!

112
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:25,166
Like... All they do is sleep.

113
00:10:25,195 --> 00:10:28,059
And that one in the front is
giving us a good view of its butt.

114
00:10:28,143 --> 00:10:29,019
Sure is.

115
00:10:29,307 --> 00:10:32,096
They aren't really doing anything,
so there's not much else to look at.

116
00:10:32,121 --> 00:10:33,950
And after all the effort we made to come out! Rude.

117
00:10:33,975 --> 00:10:35,921
I'm just glad we got to see them.

118
00:10:36,243 --> 00:10:37,094
Yeah.

119
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:39,318
Huh?

120
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:55,598
Wow!

121
