197
00:14:43,708 --> 00:14:47,012
Man, wasn't that clay self-portrait
assignment a huge pain in the butt?

198
00:14:47,096 --> 00:14:49,344
Wait, that project was due today?

199
00:14:49,425 --> 00:14:53,723
Look at that! The great, all-knowing Mio
finally forgot about her homework for once!

200
00:14:53,762 --> 00:14:56,077
Ugh! I thought it was due tomorrow!

201
00:14:56,889 --> 00:14:58,784
Mai, did you do your self-portrait?

202
00:15:01,355 --> 00:15:02,378
Ah, dang it.

203
00:15:03,971 --> 00:15:05,487
So, even Mai forgot about it!

204
00:15:05,512 --> 00:15:07,116
You don't see that every day!

205
00:15:07,559 --> 00:15:09,762
Can you not laugh at this disaster?

206
00:15:09,787 --> 00:15:12,101
But I guess you can say that when it rains,

207
00:15:12,492 --> 00:15:13,415
it pours.

208
00:15:20,476 --> 00:15:21,492
It really...

209
00:15:22,175 --> 00:15:23,749
...started pouring.

210
00:16:44,794 --> 00:16:46,422
Why you little!

211
00:16:46,607 --> 00:16:49,617
What the hell have you three done to my temple?

212
00:16:53,052 --> 00:16:54,615
You must be thieves!

213
00:16:54,777 --> 00:16:56,375
Well, not on my watch!

214
00:17:02,180 --> 00:17:04,359
That was too close!

215
00:17:10,063 --> 00:17:12,030
This must be a curse!

216
00:17:12,243 --> 00:17:15,234
You brought evil spirits to this place!

217
00:17:19,279 --> 00:17:21,394
Just get out of here.

218
00:17:22,003 --> 00:17:24,557
Leave this temple now!

219
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,259
"We should probably go,"

220
00:17:33,429 --> 00:17:35,512
is what the three girls thought,

221
00:17:35,548 --> 00:17:38,667
while being pelted by the late autumn rain.

222
00:18:17,549 --> 00:18:18,957
I'm beggin' you, Pres!

223
00:18:19,007 --> 00:18:21,067
I'm about to have a match with Mr. Takasaki

224
00:18:21,097 --> 00:18:23,347
and we need to find someone to be the referee!

225
00:18:23,444 --> 00:18:25,487
Referee for a Go+Soccer match?

226
00:18:25,512 --> 00:18:27,404
That's right. And if I can beat him,

227
00:18:27,429 --> 00:18:30,207
Mr. Takasaki said that he would become the club's advisor.

228
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:32,627
I'll win. Trust me!

229
00:18:32,729 --> 00:18:34,529
But how am I supposed to know what to do?

230
00:18:34,554 --> 00:18:35,355
Don't worry.

231
00:18:35,773 --> 00:18:37,960
Just read through that rulebook I let you borrow.

232
00:18:38,474 --> 00:18:41,170
As long as you do that, then everything is gonna be fine!

233
00:18:43,112 --> 00:18:45,430
I have no idea what's going on!

234
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:49,054
Well, I didn't even open the rulebook,
so I guess I shouldn't be surprised.

235
00:18:49,103 --> 00:18:49,937
But still!

236
00:18:50,054 --> 00:18:51,096
What are they doing?

237
00:18:51,179 --> 00:18:52,612
Is this Go+Soccer?

238
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:55,658
You wouldn't get it, even if you read the rulebook.

239
00:18:56,512 --> 00:18:57,339
Ogi!

240
00:18:58,002 --> 00:19:01,265
They're using forbidden techniques
most advanced players don't know!

241
00:19:01,382 --> 00:19:03,657
They've reached a level that defies all theory!

242
00:19:04,196 --> 00:19:06,410
Observe his stance with the outstretched arm,

243
00:19:06,516 --> 00:19:08,853
and how it represents the left leg of a Go table.

244
00:19:08,932 --> 00:19:11,837
In contrast, his opponent's stance is the stones.

245
00:19:11,937 --> 00:19:13,761
While it seems simple at a glance,

246
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,445
notice the ball between his feet.

247
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:18,031
It's just a guess, but I think they're trying...

248
00:19:19,570 --> 00:19:21,566
...to achieve the brilliance of the sun!

249
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:24,280
Where'd he get all that?

250
00:19:24,423 --> 00:19:26,017
Now I'm even more confused!

251
00:19:27,094 --> 00:19:28,215
It begins!

252
00:19:32,836 --> 00:19:33,737
Oh, no!

253
00:19:34,119 --> 00:19:35,583
And, Beloved!

254
00:19:39,221 --> 00:19:40,376
Hey, Ogi?

255
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,487
What does that even mean?

256
00:19:41,512 --> 00:19:42,301
Be quiet.

257
00:19:43,398 --> 00:19:44,475
Can't you feel it?

258
00:19:44,868 --> 00:19:46,820
The intensity between these two?

259
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,486
If they're not careful...

260
00:19:49,516 --> 00:19:50,805
...someone could die.

261
00:19:51,898 --> 00:19:53,138
Wait, what?

262
00:19:53,558 --> 00:19:55,177
How would that even happen?

263
00:19:57,052 --> 00:19:59,394
I haven't seen such high-level play in some time.

264
00:19:59,438 --> 00:20:00,745
It's quite impressive.

265
00:20:01,355 --> 00:20:04,004
No wonder the air feels so restless right now.

266
00:20:04,221 --> 00:20:05,765
Is that...? This stance.

267
00:20:05,822 --> 00:20:06,998
It can't be!

